TY  - JOUR
T1  - Finding All Solutions for a Class of Parametric Quadratic Integer Programming Problems
AU  - McBride, R. D.
AU  - Yormark, J. S.
Y1  - 1980/08/01
PY  - 1980
DA  - 1980/08/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.26.8.784
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.26.8.784
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 784
EP  - 795
VL  - 26
IS  - 8
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - We describe a practical procedure for finding all solutions to a parametric family of nonseparable quadratic integer programs that differ in their resource availabilities. We outline a new method for optimizing these quadratic integer programs, and demonstrate how to solve a sequence of such problems parametrized against the right-hand-side of a single constraint. Several methods for accelerating the basic procedure are presented, and computational experience is provided.
AB  - We describe a practical procedure for finding all solutions to a parametric family of nonseparable quadratic integer programs that differ in their resource availabilities. We outline a new method for optimizing these quadratic integer programs, and demonstrate how to solve a sequence of such problems parametrized against the right-hand-side of a single constraint. Several methods for accelerating the basic procedure are presented, and computational experience is provided.
